      "methods": [],
      "module_path": "telemetry",
      "docs": "Wire format (serde DTO) for a single JSONL event line in `track/items/<id>/logs/telemetry.jsonl`. Each variant carries the event-specific fields plus a per-line `schema_version` field per D7 (IN-08, CN-09). GateEval records gate_name, verdict, reason_summary, and duration_ms; input_hash is not recorded (AC-03, D4 user decision). reason_summary is a human-readable truncated gate-output summary bounded by the 4096-byte line limit (D3/CN-05); repository file paths may appear without redaction per OS-04 (gitignored local diagnostic log). All categorical String fields (command, gate_name, provider, model, hook_name, error_chain, timestamp, verdict, round_type) are free-form log labels or opaque values — not domain-constrained. round_type carries 'fast' or 'final' as a lowercase string rather than an enum to keep the serde DTO self-contained at the JSONL boundary and avoid coupling to the agent_profiles::RoundType enum which lacks serde derives. track_id is recorded as a plain String for the same DTO-boundary reason.",
      "spec_refs": [
